1
00:00:04,964 --> 00:00:08,425
(<i> indistinct angry voices</i> )

2
00:00:18,185 --> 00:00:19,687
Doctor?

3
00:00:19,687 --> 00:00:22,815
Oh, hello, Quark.
Oh...

4
00:00:22,815 --> 00:00:24,316
Let me guess--

5
00:00:24,316 --> 00:00:26,944
eavesdropping
on the battling O'Briens.

6
00:00:26,944 --> 00:00:28,779
Don't be ridiculous.

7
00:00:28,779 --> 00:00:30,906
Such language.

8
00:00:30,906 --> 00:00:33,492
Oh, I hope Molly's
not around.

9
00:00:33,492 --> 00:00:35,953
You can hear what they're
saying in there?

10
00:00:35,953 --> 00:00:37,371
How could I not?

11
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:39,331
Well, what are
they saying?

12
00:00:39,331 --> 00:00:43,794
Let's use a little
discretion, shall we?

13
00:00:43,794 --> 00:00:46,755
(<i> argument continues</i> )

14
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:48,883
He's done something.

15
00:00:48,883 --> 00:00:50,551
She's outraged.

16
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:52,803
He thinks she's overreacting.

17
00:00:52,803 --> 00:00:54,972
She thinks he's trying
to run her life.

18
00:00:54,972 --> 00:00:56,974
Pretty boring, actually...

19
00:00:58,642 --> 00:01:00,435
but to hear them,

20
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:03,230
you'd think it was a matter
of life and death.

21
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:04,356
Hello, Julian.

22
00:01:04,356 --> 00:01:05,816
(<i> gasps</i> )

23
00:01:05,816 --> 00:01:07,317
Hello.

24
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:08,986
Quark.

25
00:01:08,986 --> 00:01:11,572
Mrs. O'Brien.

26
00:01:11,572 --> 00:01:14,408
I thought you said
the O'Briens were
arguing in there.

27
00:01:14,408 --> 00:01:16,451
Not Miles and Keiko--

28
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:19,538
the other O'Briens,
Miles and Kira.

29
00:01:19,538 --> 00:01:21,582
What do they have
to argue about?

30
00:01:21,582 --> 00:01:23,751
Miles hid Kira's
springball racket

31
00:01:23,751 --> 00:01:25,920
because<i> she's</i>
carrying<i> his</i> baby

32
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:28,338
and he doesn't want her
taking any risks,

33
00:01:28,338 --> 00:01:30,925
and she doesn't want him
controlling her--

34
00:01:30,925 --> 00:01:32,175
(<i> voices continue</i> )

35
00:01:32,175 --> 00:01:34,344
What?

36
00:01:34,344 --> 00:01:36,638
Keiko made them stop.

37
00:01:36,638 --> 00:01:42,143
Now they're in the "let's talk
this out and share our feelings"
part of the fight.

38
00:01:42,143 --> 00:01:43,938
Show's over.

39
00:01:43,938 --> 00:01:47,024
Oh, well.
I mean, good.

40
00:01:47,024 --> 00:01:48,776
It is the power
of his voice,

41
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:50,318
the strength
of his intonation,

42
00:01:50,318 --> 00:01:52,613
that make Barak-Kadan
a great singer.

43
00:01:52,613 --> 00:01:54,114
There are none like him.

44
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:55,783
None as boring anyway.

45
00:01:55,783 --> 00:01:57,952
He never varies
his performance,

46
00:01:57,952 --> 00:02:00,079
not even
by a half-tone.

47
00:02:00,079 --> 00:02:03,331
I prefer traditional
opera performed
in the traditional manner.

48
00:02:03,331 --> 00:02:06,209
You know, for a Klingon
who was raised by humans,

49
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:10,047
wears a Starfleet uniform
and drinks prune juice,

50
00:02:10,047 --> 00:02:12,424
you're pretty attached
to tradition.

51
00:02:12,424 --> 00:02:14,509
But that's okay.

52
00:02:14,509 --> 00:02:17,137
I like a man riddled
with contradictions.

53
00:02:28,774 --> 00:02:31,443
That's
a welcome sight.

54
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:33,070
The peace talks
must be going well

55
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:34,947
if the Klingons are
back on the station.

56
00:02:34,947 --> 00:02:36,281
Worf?

57
00:02:40,661 --> 00:02:42,329
Did you see her?

58
00:02:42,329 --> 00:02:43,872
The Klingon woman?

59
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:46,875
She was glorious.

60
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:05,936
Her?

61
00:03:05,936 --> 00:03:07,604
She's okay.

62
00:03:09,106 --> 00:03:11,900
I have never
seen such a woman.

63
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:15,112
Who is she? What
House is she from?

64
00:03:15,112 --> 00:03:17,990
I do not recognize
her family crest.

65
00:03:35,423 --> 00:03:37,176
(<i> laughing</i> )

66
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:41,429
She is a friend of the Ferengi.

67
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:46,393
Now I remember who she is.

68
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:48,812
Her name is Grilka.

69
00:03:48,812 --> 00:03:52,149
And she's not just
Quark's friend...

70
00:03:52,149 --> 00:03:54,026
she's his ex-wife.

71
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:01,611
Maporian ale with just
a hint of<i>  pazafer,</i>
as I recall.

72
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:04,031
You remember.
I'm honored.

73
00:06:04,031 --> 00:06:06,407
How could I forget?
You're the only
Klingon I know

74
00:06:06,407 --> 00:06:09,953
who drinks something
besides bloodwine...
or prune juice.

75
00:06:09,953 --> 00:06:12,664
Prune juice?
Forget it.

76
00:06:13,957 --> 00:06:15,834
To the House of Grilka.

77
00:06:15,834 --> 00:06:18,461
May it continue to be
as strong and as proud

78
00:06:18,461 --> 00:06:20,463
as its lady is beautiful.

79
00:06:26,136 --> 00:06:28,429
You may not have been
the ideal husband,

80
00:06:28,429 --> 00:06:30,849
but you are an
excellent bartender.

81
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:32,684
I know of no greater
compliment.

82
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:36,313
So...

83
00:06:36,313 --> 00:06:39,983
what brings you to my
humble establishment?

84
00:06:39,983 --> 00:06:41,360
Business or pleasure?

85
00:06:47,241 --> 00:06:50,869
The recent hostilities between
the Federation and the Empire

86
00:06:50,869 --> 00:06:53,997
have been very costly
to my family.

87
00:06:53,997 --> 00:06:58,752
We have suffered great losses
in ships, lands, warriors.

88
00:06:58,752 --> 00:07:01,004
War-- what is it good for?

89
00:07:01,004 --> 00:07:03,257
If you ask me,
absolutely nothing.

90
00:07:03,257 --> 00:07:07,344
The financial cost
was significant.

91
00:07:07,344 --> 00:07:09,470
I have an idea.

92
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:12,599
Why don't I take a look
at your financial records?

93
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:14,768
I know that's not
why you're here.

94
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:17,478
I'm sure it's simply
a social visit,

95
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:18,897
but maybe I could help.

96
00:07:18,897 --> 00:07:21,775
Very well.

97
00:07:21,775 --> 00:07:27,406
If it pleases you, I will
allow you access to the records.

98
00:07:27,406 --> 00:07:29,283
Thank you.

99
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:38,208
Hear this, Ferengi.

100
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:41,836
Help Grilka and you live.

101
00:07:41,836 --> 00:07:44,005
Fail...

102
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:46,841
and I will
kill you myself.

103
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:52,472
And even though
it was an accident,

104
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:55,350
Quark took credit for killing
Grilka's husband.

105
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:56,851
Why?

106
00:07:56,851 --> 00:07:58,812
As a way of boosting
business at the bar.

107
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:00,188
And it worked.

108
00:08:00,188 --> 00:08:02,190
But then Grilka
kidnapped Quark

109
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:05,152
and took him back
to the Klingon Homeworld
and married him.

110
00:08:05,152 --> 00:08:06,569
Why?

111
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:08,405
I'm getting to that.

112
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:13,243
As a woman, Grilka was
forbidden to lead her House.

113
00:08:13,243 --> 00:08:16,663
By marrying Quark, she could
retain control through him.

114
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:19,958
Eventually, she convinced
the Council to give her control

115
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:22,710
and she divorced Quark
on the spot.

116
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:26,423
As far as I know,
that's the last time
they saw each other.

117
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:28,758
A marriage
of convenience.

118
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:30,844
Certainly for Grilka,
but I'm not sure

119
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:32,887
how convenient
it was for Quark.

120
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:35,349
His opinion is
of no consequence.

121
00:08:35,349 --> 00:08:38,601
He is unworthy of
such a prize as she.

122
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:44,399
Worf, it sounds like you have
a bad case of<i> par'Mach.</i>

123
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:46,443
SISKO:
Is that contagious?

124
00:08:49,446 --> 00:08:52,991
<i>par'Mach</i> is the
Klingon word for love,

125
00:08:52,991 --> 00:08:55,827
but with more
aggressive overtones.

126
00:08:55,827 --> 00:08:57,871
Love? Worf?

127
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:02,334
Stranger things
have happened.

128
00:09:02,334 --> 00:09:04,252
Especially around here.

129
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:14,221
This should alleviate
Kira's sneezing.
Should?

130
00:09:14,221 --> 00:09:16,806
Bajoran women have been
sneezing their way
through pregnancy

131
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:18,683
for over 100,000 years.

132
00:09:18,683 --> 00:09:21,269
You can't expect me
to cure it overnight.

133
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:26,191
You know,
I heard a rumor

134
00:09:26,191 --> 00:09:27,984
that the Jerries
might be trying

135
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:29,903
to cross the Channel
this evening.

136
00:09:29,903 --> 00:09:32,280
Maybe we should
have a surprise
waiting for them.

137
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:36,284
Serves you right.

138
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:38,619
I can't go
to the holosuite tonight.

139
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:41,206
Kira and I have some things
to work out.

140
00:09:41,206 --> 00:09:43,791
Still fighting, eh?

141
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:45,502
Who says we're fighting?

142
00:09:45,502 --> 00:09:47,170
Well, word gets around.

143
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:48,880
It's a small station.

144
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,798
It's a huge station.

145
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:53,343
Obviously
not huge enough.

146
00:09:53,343 --> 00:09:56,304
Well, for your information,
we are not fighting.

147
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:59,307
Glad to hear it.
Bajoran<i> takeo</i> herbs

148
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:00,767
for Kira's swollen ankles.

149
00:10:00,767 --> 00:10:02,561
She'll need to dissolve them

150
00:10:02,561 --> 00:10:05,146
in some kind of fruit juice
before ingesting them.

151
00:10:05,146 --> 00:10:06,814
I hope they
taste better

152
00:10:06,814 --> 00:10:08,358
than those<i> makora</i>
herbs you gave her.

153
00:10:08,358 --> 00:10:11,570
Are you sampling
all her medications?

154
00:10:11,570 --> 00:10:15,532
No...<i>  Kira</i>  didn't
like the taste.

155
00:10:15,532 --> 00:10:17,742
Oh, by the way,
I almost forgot.

156
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:19,536
She, uh...

157
00:10:19,536 --> 00:10:23,582
she has a... a rash
on the back of her thighs.

158
00:10:23,582 --> 00:10:25,542
Do you have a salve
or something?

159
00:10:25,542 --> 00:10:27,461
How long has she had it?

160
00:10:27,461 --> 00:10:29,129
Well, I noticed it yesterday

161
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:30,630
when I was helping her out
of the bathtub

162
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,173
so she's had it at least a day.

163
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:34,134
Helping her out of the tub?

164
00:10:34,134 --> 00:10:35,510
She's living in my house.

165
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:37,095
She's having my baby.

166
00:10:37,095 --> 00:10:40,265
So, uh, did you look?

167
00:10:40,265 --> 00:10:41,682
What?

168
00:10:41,682 --> 00:10:44,144
Oh, please.

169
00:10:44,144 --> 00:10:46,980
I was holding a towel up
in front of her.

170
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:52,319
How does Keiko feel about you
helping Kira out of the tub?

171
00:10:52,319 --> 00:10:56,156
Keiko feels fine about it.
You see, we are adults.

172
00:10:56,156 --> 00:10:58,825
We've developed a close,
mature relationship.

173
00:10:58,825 --> 00:11:01,328
I'm sure
that Keiko and Kira have,

174
00:11:01,328 --> 00:11:02,912
but you...

175
00:11:02,912 --> 00:11:04,664
What about me?

176
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:07,334
I'll bet you looked.

177
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:38,739
(<i> quietly</i> ):
I will apologize for
this at a later time.

178
00:11:38,739 --> 00:11:41,368
(<i> loudly</i> ):
You are in my seat!

179
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,497
Bartender!

180
00:11:45,497 --> 00:11:46,998
Bloodwine!

181
00:11:51,628 --> 00:11:55,256
What is that smell?

182
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:58,593
Is there a pile of
rotting forshak in here?

183
00:12:02,305 --> 00:12:04,265
Or is it you?

184
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:09,437
Stand when I talk to you!

185
00:12:11,022 --> 00:12:12,815
Or do you think it is funny?

186
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:14,275
<i>mev yap!</i>

187
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:19,072
Worf, son of Mogh.

188
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:23,284
Come. Join me.

189
00:12:28,665 --> 00:12:31,125
Challenging Thopok
to a fight

190
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:33,461
is a waste of time.

191
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:37,131
Grilka cannot mate
with you, now or ever.

192
00:12:37,131 --> 00:12:39,300
Your House is dishonored.

193
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,177
Your name is a curse.

194
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:42,929
I meant no disrespect.

195
00:12:42,929 --> 00:12:44,514
You showed none.

196
00:12:44,514 --> 00:12:47,141
I'm sure your motives
were honorable.

197
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:51,812
Do not let it
trouble you too much.

198
00:12:51,812 --> 00:12:54,982
In truth, I doubt it would
have been a good match.

199
00:12:56,359 --> 00:12:57,818
Why?

200
00:12:59,237 --> 00:13:02,490
Have you ever pursued
a Klingon woman?

201
00:13:04,284 --> 00:13:05,452
No.

202
00:13:05,452 --> 00:13:07,495
There's no shame in that.

203
00:13:07,495 --> 00:13:08,913
You were raised by humans.

204
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:10,457
You wear their uniform.

205
00:13:10,457 --> 00:13:12,751
You accept their values.

206
00:13:12,751 --> 00:13:15,336
How could you know anything
about our women?

207
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:18,131
You'd be surprised what I know.

208
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:19,466
Perhaps.

209
00:13:19,466 --> 00:13:22,135
But we will not
find out here.

210
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:24,471
(<i> loudly</i> ):
It is the wish
of the Lady Grilka

211
00:13:24,471 --> 00:13:27,806
that you leave us
now, son of Mogh,

212
00:13:27,806 --> 00:13:30,059
and do not return.

213
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,912
I am a fool.

214
00:13:49,912 --> 00:13:52,332
You're in love.

215
00:13:52,332 --> 00:13:55,335
Which I suppose
is the same thing.

216
00:13:55,335 --> 00:13:57,878
You're making too
much of this, Worf.

217
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,256
Tumek said that Grilka
wasn't offended.

218
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:02,592
She was probably
flattered.
There is no flattery

219
00:14:02,592 --> 00:14:05,428
in a great lady
being courted by a traitor.

220
00:14:09,140 --> 00:14:11,476
Is that what's really
bothering you?

221
00:14:11,476 --> 00:14:13,852
Or is it that Tumek said
that you didn't know

222
00:14:13,852 --> 00:14:15,522
anything about
Klingon women,

223
00:14:15,522 --> 00:14:17,440
and you're afraid
he's right?

224
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,484
(<i> door opening</i> )

225
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:22,529
What do you want?

226
00:14:22,529 --> 00:14:25,448
I want to talk to Dax,
if that's all right with you.

227
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:27,158
(<i> grumbling</i> )

228
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,497
I need help.

229
00:14:32,497 --> 00:14:34,957
Grilka invited me
to dinner,

230
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:39,295
and I need to brush up on
Klingon manners and protocol.

231
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:41,922
She invited you
to dinner?
In her quarters.

232
00:14:41,922 --> 00:14:43,800
A private dinner.

233
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,510
(<i> whispering</i> ):
A<i> very</i> private dinner.

234
00:14:48,471 --> 00:14:50,557
What's wrong with him?

235
00:14:50,557 --> 00:14:52,350
He's having a bad day.

236
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:54,602
QUARK:
Oh, that's a shame.

237
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:57,938
Well, when Grilka and I
were married,

238
00:14:57,938 --> 00:15:00,107
there wasn't a lot of, um...

239
00:15:01,192 --> 00:15:03,444
affection involved.

240
00:15:03,444 --> 00:15:06,865
So, what does a Klingon woman
expect from a man?

241
00:15:06,865 --> 00:15:09,909
Are there any secret
Klingon phrases I should know,

242
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:12,871
or do we just leap on each other
like a pair of crazed voles?

243
00:15:12,871 --> 00:15:15,874
Quark,
Klingon mating rituals

244
00:15:15,874 --> 00:15:19,377
are very... involved.

245
00:15:19,377 --> 00:15:21,254
It's not just
a one-night affair.

246
00:15:21,254 --> 00:15:22,296
Two nights.

247
00:15:23,381 --> 00:15:24,424
Whatever.

248
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:27,510
Look, I'm serious.

249
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:32,390
Grilka and I,
we have something...

250
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,934
I'm not sure what.

251
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:37,437
But I want to pursue it.
For sex?

252
00:15:37,437 --> 00:15:40,899
No!
Well, yeah, that, too.

253
00:15:40,899 --> 00:15:43,735
But there's more.

254
00:15:43,735 --> 00:15:45,570
She's glorious.

255
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:48,155
So I hear.

256
00:15:49,657 --> 00:15:52,993
Look... if you're serious
about this,

257
00:15:52,993 --> 00:15:55,371
then you have to take it
slow at dinner.

