00:28:55,568 --> 00:28:58,362
Yes. I thought
I'd take the time and relax.

510
00:28:58,362 --> 00:29:01,073
A friend of mine has a house
in the Musilla Province.

511
00:29:01,073 --> 00:29:04,535
It's quiet, remote--
no distractions.

512
00:29:04,535 --> 00:29:06,537
Perfect!
When do you leave?

513
00:29:06,537 --> 00:29:08,788
Uh, first thing in the morning.

514
00:29:08,788 --> 00:29:10,832
W-W-Wait a minute.

515
00:29:10,832 --> 00:29:15,045
You can't go alone.
What if you go into labor?

516
00:29:15,045 --> 00:29:17,715
Well, Julian doesn't think
that's going to happen
for another month.

517
00:29:17,715 --> 00:29:19,508
But he doesn't know for sure.

518
00:29:19,508 --> 00:29:21,301
Miles...

519
00:29:21,301 --> 00:29:23,554
maybe you should
go with her.

520
00:29:23,554 --> 00:29:25,305
What?
I can't go.

521
00:29:25,305 --> 00:29:27,974
I have a botanical pathology
seminar tomorrow,

522
00:29:27,974 --> 00:29:29,935
but you said yourself
things are slow in Ops.

523
00:29:29,935 --> 00:29:31,937
I don't think
that's a good idea.

524
00:29:31,937 --> 00:29:33,522
Me neither.

525
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:35,857
Miles Edward O'Brien,
are you going to let

526
00:29:35,857 --> 00:29:37,735
the woman carrying
your unborn child

527
00:29:37,735 --> 00:29:40,112
go on a trip
all by herself?

528
00:29:45,033 --> 00:29:46,785
Are you two
fighting again?

529
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:48,495
No!
Not at all.

530
00:29:48,495 --> 00:29:49,788
Good.
Then it's settled.

531
00:29:49,788 --> 00:29:51,540
Miles, let's pack your bag.

532
00:30:02,593 --> 00:30:05,178
What if I just
do what I did

533
00:30:05,178 --> 00:30:08,557
the last time a Klingon
wanted to kill me?

534
00:30:08,557 --> 00:30:10,350
I...

535
00:30:10,350 --> 00:30:13,729
throw my sword away,
kneel down in front of him

536
00:30:13,729 --> 00:30:17,149
and dare him to execute me.

537
00:30:17,149 --> 00:30:19,359
Yeah.
He'll be humiliated

538
00:30:19,359 --> 00:30:21,445
and slink away
like a scalded<i> targ.</i>

539
00:30:21,445 --> 00:30:24,197
The only reason that worked
was because Gowron stepped in

540
00:30:24,197 --> 00:30:26,659
and restrained your opponent
before he was able to kill you.

541
00:30:26,659 --> 00:30:28,243
No one will stop Thopok.

542
00:30:28,243 --> 00:30:30,329
Dax and I aren't even
able to attend.

543
00:30:30,329 --> 00:30:33,540
So my choices are
to not show up,

544
00:30:33,540 --> 00:30:35,959
be branded a coward
and lose Grilka...

545
00:30:35,959 --> 00:30:37,877
or die?
Yes.

546
00:30:37,877 --> 00:30:41,423
Oh, come on now! There must
be another way out of this!

547
00:30:41,423 --> 00:30:44,134
You people have
rituals for everything

548
00:30:44,134 --> 00:30:45,927
except waste extraction.

549
00:30:45,927 --> 00:30:49,181
You must have a ceremony
or a secret handshake

550
00:30:49,181 --> 00:30:51,266
or something I can do?

551
00:30:57,105 --> 00:30:58,607
I have an idea.

552
00:30:59,775 --> 00:31:01,568
(<i> grunting</i> )

553
00:31:19,002 --> 00:31:22,506
Oh, congratulations.

554
00:31:22,506 --> 00:31:24,424
How do you feel?

555
00:31:24,424 --> 00:31:26,134
Like a puppet...

556
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:28,220
and I have some complaints
for the puppeteer.

557
00:31:28,220 --> 00:31:30,263
You nearly wrenched my
arm out of its socket.

558
00:31:30,263 --> 00:31:32,015
The movement
would not have hurt

559
00:31:32,015 --> 00:31:33,642
if you were in better
physical condition.

560
00:31:33,642 --> 00:31:35,602
Exercise makes me sweat.

561
00:31:35,602 --> 00:31:38,938
(<i> chuckling</i> ):
You need to get
some sleep.

562
00:31:40,607 --> 00:31:42,651
If your body's
tired tomorrow,

563
00:31:42,651 --> 00:31:45,237
Worf won't even be
able to save you.

564
00:31:45,237 --> 00:31:46,446
Bedtime.

565
00:31:46,446 --> 00:31:47,531
Mm-hmm.

566
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:53,119
I cannot believe the lengths
I'm going to for that Ferengi.

567
00:31:53,119 --> 00:31:56,081
I'm practically
giving him Grilka.

568
00:31:56,081 --> 00:31:59,418
What is it
you see in her, anyway?

569
00:31:59,418 --> 00:32:03,422
I mean, she's attractive,
but other than that?

570
00:32:03,422 --> 00:32:06,299
It is everything
about her...

571
00:32:06,299 --> 00:32:08,301
the way she
carries herself,

572
00:32:08,301 --> 00:32:09,887
confident and strong.

573
00:32:09,887 --> 00:32:12,890
She commands
those around her.

574
00:32:12,890 --> 00:32:14,683
The proud tilt
of her head...

575
00:32:14,683 --> 00:32:17,770
the way her face betrays
none of her true feelings...

576
00:32:17,770 --> 00:32:20,731
the power of her voice.

577
00:32:20,731 --> 00:32:24,902
And her eyes-- as hard
as separ gemstones,

578
00:32:24,902 --> 00:32:26,737
and twice as sharp.

579
00:32:26,737 --> 00:32:29,406
Sounds like you're
describing a statue.

580
00:32:29,406 --> 00:32:32,284
What would you do
with a woman like that--

581
00:32:32,284 --> 00:32:35,161
put her up on a pedestal
and clean her every week?

582
00:32:35,161 --> 00:32:37,247
You do not understand.

583
00:32:37,247 --> 00:32:40,667
If I were in your shoes,
I would be looking for someone

584
00:32:40,667 --> 00:32:45,338
a little more entertaining,
a little more fun,

585
00:32:45,338 --> 00:32:47,633
and maybe even

586
00:32:47,633 --> 00:32:50,135
a little more
attainable.

587
00:32:50,135 --> 00:32:52,638
You are not in my shoes.

588
00:32:52,638 --> 00:32:53,931
Too bad.

589
00:32:53,931 --> 00:32:55,641
You'd be amazed
at what I can do

590
00:32:55,641 --> 00:32:58,226
in a pair of size 18 boots.

591
00:33:16,787 --> 00:33:18,664
He's in position.

592
00:33:21,374 --> 00:33:25,170
Quark, son of Keldar,
why are you here?

593
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:28,674
To... to ans...

594
00:33:28,674 --> 00:33:31,343
(<i> electronic beeping begins</i> )

595
00:33:34,638 --> 00:33:37,015
To answer the challenge
of Thopok,

596
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:40,101
to prove my honor...

597
00:33:40,101 --> 00:33:41,770
and to win the favor

598
00:33:41,770 --> 00:33:43,689
of the Lady Grilka.

599
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:53,824
The challenge has been given
and accepted.

600
00:33:53,824 --> 00:33:56,618
Let no one interfere!

601
00:33:58,077 --> 00:33:59,329
<i>Mok!</i>

602
00:34:15,804 --> 00:34:17,514
(<i> yelling</i> )

603
00:34:28,775 --> 00:34:30,569
Where did you learn to
fight with a<i> bat'leth?</i>

604
00:34:30,569 --> 00:34:33,363
I'm a man of many talents.

605
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:53,675
(<i> chuckling fiendishly</i> )

606
00:34:56,887 --> 00:34:58,972
(<i> equipment powering down</i> )

607
00:35:05,729 --> 00:35:06,772
No!

608
00:35:06,772 --> 00:35:08,356
Wait!

609
00:35:08,356 --> 00:35:10,233
You damaged the
optronic relay.

610
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:11,860
Can you repair it?

611
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:14,320
I don't know.

612
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:15,989
Well?!

613
00:35:15,989 --> 00:35:19,743
I claim the Right
of... Proclamation.

614
00:35:21,661 --> 00:35:24,539
I've never heard
of the "Right of Proclamation."

615
00:35:24,539 --> 00:35:27,459
It is a Ferengi custom.
Then it has no place here!

616
00:35:27,459 --> 00:35:29,419
I beg to differ!

617
00:35:29,419 --> 00:35:32,589
I am as proud of my heritage
as your are of yours,

618
00:35:32,589 --> 00:35:34,466
and I will not
be denied

619
00:35:34,466 --> 00:35:36,593
the opportunity
to express myself

620
00:35:36,593 --> 00:35:39,471
according to Ferengi custom.

621
00:35:39,471 --> 00:35:43,266
(<i> growls</i> )
He has shown respect
to our traditions.

622
00:35:43,266 --> 00:35:45,978
We will do the same.

623
00:35:48,688 --> 00:35:50,398
What do you need to do?

624
00:35:51,608 --> 00:35:55,112
I must... make a speech.

625
00:35:55,112 --> 00:35:56,655
About what?

626
00:35:56,655 --> 00:35:58,824
About you.

627
00:35:58,824 --> 00:36:00,826
Get on with it!

628
00:36:00,826 --> 00:36:05,204
I do not know how,
but he is still alive.

629
00:36:05,204 --> 00:36:06,915
You must work faster.

630
00:36:06,915 --> 00:36:09,167
I'm going as fast as I can.

631
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:10,460
Uh...

632
00:36:12,754 --> 00:36:16,800
to this end...
my blade soars...

633
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:20,512
through the...
aquarium of my soul,

634
00:36:20,512 --> 00:36:24,016
seeking the kelp
of discontent

635
00:36:24,016 --> 00:36:29,104
which must be caught
so that the rocky bottom of love

636
00:36:29,104 --> 00:36:31,857
lie in waiting with...

637
00:36:31,857 --> 00:36:34,067
fertile sand

638
00:36:34,067 --> 00:36:35,777
for the coming seed

639
00:36:35,777 --> 00:36:37,988
of Grilka's affection.

640
00:36:37,988 --> 00:36:44,452
And yet, does this explain
my need for her?

641
00:36:44,452 --> 00:36:45,996
No.

642
00:36:45,996 --> 00:36:49,791
It is like a giant
cave of emptiness

643
00:36:49,791 --> 00:36:55,130
waiting for the bats
of love to hang by...

644
00:36:59,092 --> 00:37:02,971
Well, I guess that's
enough talking.

645
00:37:04,890 --> 00:37:07,266
Now, back to the fighting.

646
00:37:07,266 --> 00:37:08,768
No showing off
this time, Worf.

647
00:37:08,768 --> 00:37:10,145
Just get it
over with.

648
00:37:10,145 --> 00:37:12,189
I was not showing off.

649
00:37:12,189 --> 00:37:14,607
(<i> grunting</i> )

650
00:37:14,607 --> 00:37:15,901
(<i> grunts</i> )

651
00:37:15,901 --> 00:37:16,985
(<i> grunts</i> )

652
00:37:18,277 --> 00:37:20,238
End it!

653
00:37:20,238 --> 00:37:22,448
If you insist.

654
00:37:26,161 --> 00:37:27,662
(<i> grunts</i> )

655
00:37:31,750 --> 00:37:33,835
Maybe not.

656
00:37:33,835 --> 00:37:35,670
Maybe...

657
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:41,718
I'll just pick up
your sword and...

658
00:37:55,065 --> 00:37:57,358
Give it to you... I guess.

659
00:38:02,072 --> 00:38:05,450
Thopok, your honor
is satisfied.

660
00:38:05,450 --> 00:38:07,410
I return your weapon

661
00:38:07,410 --> 00:38:10,247
and discharge you
from my House.

662
00:38:22,884 --> 00:38:24,136
My lady.

663
00:38:24,136 --> 00:38:25,511
(<i> exhales heavily</i> )

664
00:38:27,973 --> 00:38:31,768
<i>Do-MACH ah chee ghos</i>
<i>eh-PAGH?</i>

665
00:38:31,768 --> 00:38:32,852
(<i> grunts</i> )

666
00:38:40,110 --> 00:38:42,487
(<i> yells</i> )

667
00:38:47,159 --> 00:38:50,620
Congratulations.
You did it.

668
00:38:50,620 --> 00:38:53,915
What does she see
in that parasite?

669
00:38:53,915 --> 00:38:56,918
Who knows? But they're
on the same wavelength,

670
00:38:56,918 --> 00:39:00,463
and at least Quark
can see an opportunity when
it's standing in front of him.

671
00:39:00,463 --> 00:39:03,091
He would have to be
blind not to see it.

672
00:39:06,594 --> 00:39:08,805
<i>MoVas ah-kee rustak.</i>

673
00:39:11,390 --> 00:39:13,726
Computer,<i> bat'leth.</i>

674
00:39:16,980 --> 00:39:19,565
<i>MoVas ah-kee rustak.</i>

675
00:39:21,901 --> 00:39:27,157
<i>Kosh tomaH...</i>
<i>ehpaq kaVeir Lukara.</i>

676
00:39:27,157 --> 00:39:30,368
<i>Ish-tovee chuCH</i>
<i>thling nuq?</i>

677
00:39:35,081 --> 00:39:37,500
<i>Meklo boH ka Mech.</i>

678
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:41,004
<i>Te-doQ roos ka</i>
<i>Mech-TOH.</i>

679
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,344
Oh!

680
00:39:50,805 --> 00:39:52,974
(<i> both grunting</i> )

681
00:39:58,855 --> 00:40:00,315
So I guess we're going.

682
00:40:00,315 --> 00:40:01,691
Looks like it.

683
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:11,659
Tell me about this...
this house we're going to.

684
00:40:11,659 --> 00:40:15,955
It's a gorgeous
200-year-old cottage.

685
00:40:15,955 --> 00:40:17,665
It's filled
with antiques,

686
00:40:17,665 --> 00:40:20,835
sitting in the middle
of a deep, dark forest.

687
00:40:20,835 --> 00:40:24,214
It's got three fireplaces,
two balconies.
I see.

688
00:40:24,214 --> 00:40:27,592
It's, uh, 20 kilometers
from the nearest neighbor,

689
00:40:27,592 --> 00:40:29,177
30 to the nearest town.

690
00:40:29,177 --> 00:40:31,304
(<i> laughs</i> ):
Why am I not
surprised?

691
00:40:31,304 --> 00:40:35,433
It gets worse.
There's a view.

692
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:37,185
Of what?
Of the Holana River.

693
00:40:37,185 --> 00:40:39,604
You can see it from every room
in the house,

694
00:40:39,604 --> 00:40:41,773
and at night,
when the stars are out,

695
00:40:41,773 --> 00:40:44,609
and you can only hear
rushing water.

696
00:40:44,609 --> 00:40:48,780
It may be one of the most
romantic spots in all of Bajor.

697
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:52,117
That's it.
I'm not going.

698
00:40:52,117 --> 00:40:55,203
I don't care what Keiko says,
I'm not going. You go.

699
00:40:55,203 --> 00:40:58,539
I'll wait an hour
and then I'll, I'll tell her
that you left without me.

700
00:40:58,539 --> 00:41:00,583
That there was
a miscommunication
about the departure time.

701
00:41:00,583 --> 00:41:02,668
You think she'll buy it?
She'll probably accuse us

702
00:41:02,668 --> 00:41:04,796
of having another fight,
of behaving like children,

703
00:41:04,796 --> 00:41:06,923
but I can handle that.
The important thing is

704
00:41:06,923 --> 00:41:10,176
that we don't go anywhere
near that place together.

705
00:41:10,176 --> 00:41:12,804
You are absolutely right.

706
00:41:12,804 --> 00:41:14,973
In fact, I'm going
to go to the capital

707
00:41:14,973 --> 00:41:16,474
and see Shakaar.

708
00:41:16,474 --> 00:41:19,102
That's the best idea
you've had all week.

709
00:41:24,190 --> 00:41:25,900
Have a good trip.

710
00:41:25,900 --> 00:41:27,402
Thanks.

711
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:33,074
It would've been nice.

712
00:41:34,909 --> 00:41:36,369
In another life.

713
00:41:37,578 --> 00:41:39,038
Let's not even think
about it.

714
00:41:39,038 --> 00:41:40,748
All right.
Let's not.

715
00:41:44,502 --> 00:41:45,753
Miles...?

716
00:41:45,753 --> 00:41:47,672
Yes, Nerys?

717
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:50,425
Get out.

718
00:41:51,634 --> 00:41:53,219
Right.

719
00:41:55,972 --> 00:41:57,640
(<i> sighs</i> )

720
00:41:57,640 --> 00:42:00,059
A compound fracture
of the right radius,

721
00:42:00,059 --> 00:42:03,188
two fractured ribs,
torn ligaments,

722
00:42:03,188 --> 00:42:06,232
strained tendons,
numerous contusions,

723
00:42:06,232 --> 00:42:09,694
bruises and scratches.
What have you been doing?

724
00:42:09,694 --> 00:42:14,115
You mean,
what have<i> we</i> been doing?

725
00:42:14,115 --> 00:42:16,701
(<i> both laugh</i> )

726
00:42:16,701 --> 00:42:18,953
Never mind.

727
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:21,164
I don't need
that particular image

728
00:42:21,164 --> 00:42:22,748
running around my head.

729
00:42:22,748 --> 00:42:24,334
I'll just treat you.

730
00:42:25,502 --> 00:42:26,878
(<i> door opens</i> )

731
00:42:26,878 --> 00:42:28,463
What happened to you two?

732
00:42:29,839 --> 00:42:32,300
We, um...

733
00:42:32,300 --> 00:42:35,303
Well, um, if you
must know...

734
00:42:35,303 --> 00:42:36,929
No!

735
00:42:36,929 --> 00:42:40,683
No, uh...
I don't need that image either.

736
00:42:40,683 --> 00:42:43,019
In fact, I'm going to stop
asking that question altogether.

737
00:42:43,019 --> 00:42:45,230
People can come in,
I will treat them,

738
00:42:45,230 --> 00:42:46,939
and that's all.

739
00:42:46,939 --> 00:42:49,692
Please... have a seat.

740
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:51,861
I'll be with you in a minute.

741
00:43:06,751 --> 00:43:09,379
(<i> both sigh</i> )

742
00:43:12,465 --> 00:43:15,051
You do realize
that, according to
Klingon tradition--

743
00:43:15,051 --> 00:43:18,012
According to tradition,
we have to get married.

744
00:43:18,012 --> 00:43:19,889
But, as you
keep insisting,

745
00:43:19,889 --> 00:43:21,849
you are not a
traditional woman.

746
00:43:23,809 --> 00:43:27,063
The truth is, Worf,

747
00:43:27,063 --> 00:43:31,109
at heart, you're not
much of a traditional man.

748
00:43:34,404 --> 00:43:36,781
You might be right.

749
00:43:36,781 --> 00:43:38,866
How do you wish
to proceed?

750
00:43:40,577 --> 00:43:42,287
I don't know.

751
00:43:42,287 --> 00:43:44,205
You must have some idea.

752
00:43:44,205 --> 00:43:45,748
You were the...

753
00:43:45,748 --> 00:43:47,875
Aggressor?
Yes.

754
00:43:47,875 --> 00:43:49,586
And now there
are questions

755
00:43:49,586 --> 00:43:51,045
that must be answered.

756
00:43:55,841 --> 00:43:57,302
Mmm.

757
00:43:57,302 --> 00:43:59,554
I don't feel like
answering questions.

758
00:44:01,055 --> 00:44:04,183
Why don't we just take it
one day at a time

759
00:44:04,183 --> 00:44:05,726
and see what happens?

760
00:44:10,815 --> 00:44:13,859
I, uh, do not like
the uncertainty

761
00:44:13,859 --> 00:44:15,403
of that arrangement.

762
00:44:17,530 --> 00:44:20,158
One thing's for certain...

763
00:44:20,158 --> 00:44:23,035
you've stopped thinking
about Grilka.

764
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:29,417
(<i> both laughing</i> )
